Shared Qs (solve_linsys)


  1. Question

    Solve the system: \[y = \frac{3 x}{2} + 4\] \[y = - 4 x - 7\]

    Your answers:

    • \(x=\)
    • \(y=\)


    Solution

    Eliminate \(y\) by subtrating the second equation from the first. \[0 = \frac{11 x}{2} + 11\]

    Subtract 11 from both sides.

    \[-11 = \frac{11 x}{2}\]

    Multiply/divide to solve for \(x\).

    \[x = -2\]

    Plug in -2 for \(x\) in either original equation.

    \[y = \frac{3 (-2)}{2} + 4\]

    \[y = 1\]

    You can also solve this by graphing!




  2. Question

    Solve the system: \[y = x - 6\] \[y = 4 - 4 x\]

    Your answers:

    • \(x=\)
    • \(y=\)


    Solution

    Eliminate \(y\) by subtrating the second equation from the first. \[0 = 5 x - 10\]

    Subtract -10 from both sides.

    \[10 = 5 x\]

    Multiply/divide to solve for \(x\).

    \[x = 2\]

    Plug in 2 for \(x\) in either original equation.

    \[y = (2) - 6\]

    \[y = -4\]

    You can also solve this by graphing!
